    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-09-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="17"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Von Callenberg</persName>
                    </hi>,</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-09-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 16, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have charged the United States minister at Vienna to make on behalf of the
                    President suitable acknowledgment of the sympathetic <pb facs="0095" n="15"
                        xml:id="pg_15"/> message of His Imperial and Royal Majesty which you
                    conveyed by your telegram of the 15th instant.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
